The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for the dynamic multichannel access problem, which involves making decisions in a partially observable Markov decision process. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper considers a time-varying environment, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also compares its framework to a Deep-Q network (DQN) based framework, which suggests that it may be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves making decisions under uncertainty, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
